= Extracted Lists
<extracted-lists>
The list environments below are extracted from arXiv LaTeX source and
wrapped for pdfLaTeX validation.

/ i): #block[
it is composed, at large distances, by #mi(`D-2`) free bosons,
describing the transverse displacements of the string;
]

/ ii): #block[
each bosonic field is compactified on a circle of radius #mi(`R_t`)
related to the finite thickness of the flux tube. This allows
fermionizing the model, which in turn guarantees that the colour flux
tube does not self-overlap;
]

/ iii): #block[
the boundary conditions on quark lines are dictated by the lattice gauge
theory (LGT) and fulfil a sort of orthogonality constraint such that,
whenever the quark and antiquark lines coincide, the effective string
vanishes . This forces the adimensional radius
#mi(`\nu=\sqrt{\pi\sigma}R_t`) to be exactly #mi(`\nu=1/4`).
]
